Simple example to show how to build an Hello World android app from the command line

# get stack ready
Using the Android and Gradle stack
1. git clone http://github.com/godfreynolan/codio in the workspace directory 
2. android list sdk --all in the android-sdk-linux directory
3. install the build tools, SDK etc for API-23
4. android update sdk -u -a -t "n1, n2, n3" to get all the APIs downloaded
5. chmod +x gradlew in the helloworld build directory 
6. change compileSdkVersion to 23 and buildToolsVersion to "23.0.1" in build.gradle
7. Add the following to the build.gradle file   
   android {                                                                                                                                                             
      lintOptions {                                                                                                                                                     
          abortOnError false                                                                                                                                            
      }                                                                                                                                                                 
  }  
8. run ./gradlew build 